EXHIBIT A TO SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
Shared Facilities The “Shared Facilities” shall consist of: Interconnection Customer’s Interconnection Facilities: 34.5 kV to 345 kV transformation substation with associated 34.5 kV and 345 kV switchgear; One 345 kV overhead transmission line to the Point of Interconnection and Point of Change of Ownership with the Transmission Owner Reactive power compensation equipment to maintain 95% lagging (providing VARs) and 95% leading (absorbing VARs) power factor at the Point of Interconnection; and All necessary relay, protection, control and communications systems required to protect Interconnection Customer’s Interconnection Facilities and Generating Facility and coordinate with Transmission Owner’s relay, protection, control, and communications systems. Miscellaneous Communications Equipment: Onsite communications equipment used by Seiling Interconnection, Seiling I and Seiling II that the Parties reasonably require use of in connection with operations of the Projects, together with any replacement, expansions, modifications, improvements or additions to any of the foregoing.

SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”), is entered into as of September 16, 2014 (the “Effective Date”), by and between Seiling Wind Interconnection Services, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Seiling Interconnection”), Seiling Wind, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Seiling I”), and Seiling Wind II, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Seiling II”, and together with Seiling Interconnection and Seiling I, the “Parties” and each a “Party”). RECITALS WHEREAS, Seiling I is developing and will own and operate a wind energy generation facility with a nameplate capacity of 200 MW (net) (the “Seiling I Project”); WHEREAS, Seiling II is developing and will own and operate a wind energy generation facility with a nameplate capacity of 100 MW (net) (the “Seiling II Project”, together with the Seiling I Project, the “Projects” and each a “Project”); WHEREAS, Seiling Interconnection is party to a certain Generator Interconnection Agreement by and among itself, Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (“SPP”) and Oklahoma Gas & Electric Company (“OGE”), (the “GIA”) which provides for Interconnection Services (as defined in the GIA) for a Generating Facility with an aggregate capacity not to exceed 300 MW ; WHEREAS, Seiling Interconnection owns certain personal property, fixtures, equipment and/or facilities (including certain of the Interconnection Customer’s Interconnection Facilities, as identified in Appendix A to the GIA) described in Exhibit A attached hereto (the “Shared Facilities”) that are necessary to interconnect the Projects to the electric transmission system of OGE; WHEREAS, Seiling I, Seiling II and Seiling Interconnection are entering into this Shared Facilities Agreement to allow Seiling I and Seiling II to use the Shared Facilities and to enable Seiling I and Seiling II to be able to inject the output of the Projects into the electric transmission system of OGE; and NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows: AGREEMENT TERM; EARLY TERMINATION Term. The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue for an initial term of 10 years, with automatic 1-year extensions thereafter, until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties, or (b) pursuant to Section 1.2 of this Agreement. Early Termination. This Agreement shall automatically terminate, without further action by either Party and without further liability of any Party to any other Party (except for obligations accruing prior to the termination), upon the date that both Seiling I and Seiling II, or their successors and assigns, shall have permanently ceased operation of the Projects for the production of electric energy. GRANT OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS Grant. Seiling Interconnection hereby grants to Seiling I and Seiling II, respectively, during the term of this Agreement, and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with the Interconnection Service received by Seiling Interconnection from SPP and OGE, and ownership, operation and maintenance of the Seiling I and Seiling II Projects, respectively. Essential Nature. Seiling Interconnection hereby acknowledges that the right of Seiling I and Seiling II to access and utilize the Shared Facilities are essential to the production and delivery of electric energy from the Seiling I and Seiling II Projects to the electric transmission system of OGE. Vesting. The right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities granted hereunder by Seiling Interconnection to Seiling I and Seiling II, respectively, shall vest in each of Seiling I and Seiling II, respectively, as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title, leasehold or other interest or rights in the Shared Facilities. 2.4 License Fee. In consideration of the right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities, Seiling I and Seiling II agree to pay to Seiling Interconnection a one-time license fee (the “License Fee”) based on Seiling I and Seiling II’s pro rata share of the total, aggregate costs, fee and expenses incurred by Seiling Interconnection for development, real estate rights, and engineering, procurement and construction of the Shared Facilities, with such pro rata share calculated based on the MW capacity owned by Seiling I (66.7 %) and Seiling II (33.3%) as against the overall MW capacity of generating facilities using the Shared Facilities. Any previous payments between the Parties relating to these costs, fees and expenses shall be applied against payments due under this section. NATURE OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS Nature of Services. Seiling Interconnection shall provide certain services to Seiling I and Seiling II consisting of those services Seiling Interconnection receives through the GIA, as necessary to enable the energy generated by the Seiling I Project and Seiling II Project to reach the Transmission System. The Parties acknowledge that the grant of rights under this Agreement by Seiling Interconnection to Seiling I and Seiling II is made for the purpose of enabling the energy from Seiling I to Seiling II to reach the transmission system of OGE. For the avoidance of doubt, the grant of rights under this Agreement by Seiling Interconnection to Seiling I and Seiling II shall not relieve Seiling Interconnection of its obligations under the GIA. Obligations of Seiling Interconnection. Seiling Interconnection shall exercise its rights, provide the service under this Agreement, and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner consistent with its obligations under the GIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Seiling Interconnection agrees to: perform its obligations under this Agreement and the GIA in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the GIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the GIA; comply with all provisions of the GIA to which it is subject (and all insurance requirements, payments due, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof); promptly provide to Seiling I and Seiling II any notices it receives under the GIA from SPP or OGE, including any notices regarding emergencies under Article 13 of the GIA; not take any action, without Seiling I’s and Seiling II’s written consent, to terminate the GIA. perform necessary maintenance on the Shared Facilities, as agreed to in this Agreement; and ensure that, to the maximum extent practicable, any actions by Seiling II that may, or do, cause Seiling Interconnection to fail to comply with the GIA, do not affect the Service received by Seiling I hereunder; and ensure that, to the maximum extent practicable, any actions by Seiling I that may, or do, cause Seiling Interconnection to fail to comply with the GIA, do not affect the Service received by Seiling II hereunder. Obligations of Seiling I. Seiling I shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is reasonable and facilitates Seiling Interconnection’s performance under, and compliance with, the GIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Seiling I agrees to: operate the Seiling I Project in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the GIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the GIA; facilitate Seiling Interconnection’s compliance with all provisions of the GIA (including, without limitation, all insurance requirements, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof) as related to the Seiling I Project; not take any action (or refrain from taking any action) which would result in a breach of the GIA by Seiling Interconnection; use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of the Seiling I Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default under the GIA, and if such default occurs, to promptly assist Seiling Interconnection to cure such default in accordance with the terms of the GIA; comply with all instructions, as may be communicated to it by Seiling Interconnection, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the GIA with respect to the Seiling I Project; provide Seiling Interconnection with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of the Seiling I Project required for Seiling Interconnection to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the GIA; and provide promptly to Seiling Interconnection copies of all notices and instructions received by it that affect Seiling Interconnection’s performance under the GIA. Obligations of Seiling II. Seiling II shall exercise its rights and perform its obligations under this Agreement in a manner that is reasonable and facilitates Seiling Interconnection’s performance under, and compliance with, the GIA. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, during the term of this Agreement, Seiling II agrees to: operate the Seiling II Project in accordance with Good Utility Practice, Applicable Laws and Regulations and Applicable Reliability Standards, in each case as defined in the GIA, and in a manner consistent with the terms of the GIA; facilitate Seiling Interconnection’s compliance with all provisions of the GIA (including, without limitation, all insurance requirements, operational limits, operating guides, operating procedures and reliability standards and requirements applicable by virtue thereof) as related to the Seiling II Project; not take any action (or refrain from taking any action) which would result in a breach of the GIA by Seiling Interconnection; use all commercially reasonable efforts to promptly resolve any technical issues arising in connection with the operation of the Seiling II Project that might reasonably be expected to result in a default under the GIA, and if such default occurs, to promptly assist Seiling Interconnection to cure such default in accordance with the terms of the GIA; comply with all instructions, as may be communicated to it by Seiling Interconnection, in order to ensure compliance with the provisions of the GIA with respect to the Seiling II Project; provide Seiling Interconnection with all reasonable information regarding the operation and condition of the Seiling II Project required for Seiling Interconnection to maintain compliance with the terms and conditions of the GIA; and provide promptly to Seiling Interconnection copies of all notices and instructions received by it that affect Seiling Interconnection’s performance under the GIA. No Joint and Several Liability between Seiling I and Seiling II. The Parties acknowledge that this Agreement does not subject Seiling I to joint and several liability for any actions taken by Seiling II, and conversely does not subject Seiling II to joint and several liability for any actions taken by Seiling I. Assignment or Transfer of Rights. Except as set forth in Section 9.6 hereof, Seiling I and Seiling II, respectively, shall not assign or transfer any rights granted to such Party hereunder with regard to the Shared Facilities, or grant any permission, license, right of way or similar right with regard to the Shared Facilities, without the prior written consent of Seiling Interconnection. Interference. Subject to the terms of this Agreement, in no event shall any Party be entitled to exercise its rights to access and utilize the Shared Facilities if the exercise of such rights would materially interfere with or limit the reasonable and necessary access and utilization of the Shared Facilities by any other Party. Prior Written Consent. Except as set forth in this Agreement, Seiling Interconnection shall not take any action that results in the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of the respective rights or increases the obligations or responsibilities of Seiling I and Seiling II of access to, utilization of or reliance upon the Shared Facilities without the prior written consent of Seiling I and Seiling II. MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES Allocation of Certain Costs and Expenses. Seiling Interconnection shall be responsible for the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities; provided, however, that the Parties hereby agree that (a) the costs and expenses of the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities and of insuring the Shared Facilities, and (b) costs that Seiling Interconnection is responsible for under the GIA, including potential costs under section 10.5 for operations and maintenance expenses, and which are not directly caused by only either Seiling I or Seiling II, shall be shared between Seiling I and Seiling II on a pro rata basis, with Seiling I paying 66.7% of the costs and expenses and Seiling II paying 33.3% of the costs and expenses. Each of Seiling I and Seiling II shall pay its respective allocation (specified above) of such costs and expenses to Seiling Interconnection within ten (10) days of receipt from Seiling Interconnection of each written notice specifying such costs and expenses. Seiling I and Seiling II shall each be liable to pay for the station power service of their respective Projects. Successor Agreement. In the event that the Shared Facilities are no longer operated and maintained by a single entity for any reason, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement) that specifies the division of responsibilities of the entities providing operation and maintenance services associated with the Shared Facilities. CHANGE IN LAW Change in Law. In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the Shared Facilities, any of the Projects, or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal, state or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement. CERTAIN COVENANTS Authority and Operational Abilities. Each of the Parties represents, as of the Effective Date, and covenants for the term of this Agreement, that such Party has the legal authority and operational abilities to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement. Agreement to Cooperate. Each Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with the other Parties so that, subject to the terms of this Agreement, each Project benefits from the full utilization and enjoyment of the Shared Facilities as is necessary for the efficient operation of each such Project. Adverse Events. If an operational issue arises at the Seiling I Project or Seiling II Project that is reasonably expected to result in a material breach by Seiling Interconnection of the GIA or this Agreement (an “Adverse Event”), Seiling Interconnection shall curtail the Project that is causing the Adverse Event. In the event of such curtailment, energy deliveries to the Point of Interconnection from the Project that has caused the Adverse Event shall be limited as necessary until the Adverse Event has been cured in the reasonable judgment of Seiling Interconnection. If, as a direct result of an Adverse Event caused by the Seiling I Project or the Seiling II Project, Seiling Interconnection incurs costs, expenses, or penalties of any kind (“AE Costs”), Seiling I or Seiling II, as applicable, shall be solely responsible for reimbursing Seiling Interconnection for such AE Costs. In the event that both Projects are responsible for the Adverse Event, and to the extent that Seiling Interconnection, in its sole and absolute discretion, can accurately allocate responsibility for such Adverse Event between the Projects, Seiling I shall be responsible for only its allocable portion of such applicable AE Costs and Seiling II shall be responsible for only its allocable portion of such applicable AE Costs. If, however, it is not reasonably possible for Seiling Interconnection, as determined in its sole and absolute discretion, to accurately allocate such responsibility, Seiling I shall be liable for 66.7% of such AE Costs, and Seiling II shall be liable for 33.3% of such AE Costs. Priority of Curtailment. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, in the event of curtailment pursuant to the GIA (or pursuant to applicable operating guides or applicable reliability standards and requirements), Seiling Interconnection shall curtail the Seiling I and Seiling II Projects as follows: first, and if necessary in full, any Project (if any) the operation of which is contributing to an OGE or SPP system emergency; and thereafter, both Projects, at the same time and to an extent for each Project equal to such Project’s pro rata portion (based on such Project’s nameplate capacity) of the energy delivered to the Point of Interconnection as of the time immediately prior to the event giving rise to the curtailment. MATERIAL BREACH; LIMITATIONS Material Breach by any Party. In the event of any material breach of this Agreement by any Party and such Party fails to cure promptly such breach within a reasonable time not to exceed thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice from any other, non-defaulting Party describing such breach, the non-defaulting Party shall have the right, but not the obligation, in addition to all remedies available to it at law or in equity, to (i) cure the breach on behalf of the defaulting Party, or (ii) suspend the breaching Party’s access to all or any portion of the Shared Facilities owned by such non-breaching Party for so long as such default shall be continuing and remain uncured. Notwithstanding the foregoing, in the event that a breach of this Agreement could give rise to a breach by Seiling Interconnection pursuant to the terms of the GIA, the non-defaulting Party shall not be required to provide the defaulting Party with notice and/or an opportunity to cure in order to exercise the remedies specified in clause (i) or (ii) above; provided, that the remedy specified in clause (i) may be exercised, without prejudice to any right or remedy of any Party hereunder, by any lender of such Party. If a Party (or any lender thereof) chooses to cure a Party’s default, the defaulting Party shall reimburse the non-defaulting Party (or such Party’s lender) upon demand for all commercially reasonable costs incurred by the non-defaulting Party (or such Party’s lender) in curing such default. Except for indemnification obligations related to third-party claims as provided for in Section 9.7, in no event shall any Party be liable under any provision of this Agreement for any losses, damages, costs or expenses for any special, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages including, but not limited to, loss of profit or revenue, loss of the use of equipment, cost of capital, cost of temporary equipment or services, whether based in whole or in part in contract, in tort, including negligence, strict liability, or any other theory of liability. FORCE MAJEURE Force Majeure. In the event of an act of God, government order or restraint, war (declared or undeclared) or warlike conditions, act of terrorism, blockade, revolution, strike, lockout, civil commotion, fire, flood, storm, epidemic or any other occurrence beyond a Party’s reasonable control (each a “Force Majeure Event”), such Party shall promptly notify each other Party thereof and, so long as such condition shall persist, such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement caused directly or indirectly thereby. The claiming Party shall give each other Party notice describing the particulars of the Force Majeure Event. Within fifteen (15) days after giving notice of the Force Majeure Event, the claiming Party shall give each other Party an estimate of the Force Majeure Event’s expected duration and probable impact. The claiming Party shall continue to furnish each other Party with timely regular reports during the continuation of the Force Majeure Event. Each Party shall promptly exercise commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit the impact to its obligations hereunder as a result of the Force Majeure Event. MISCELLANEOUS Relationship of Parties. The Parties do not intend to create hereby any joint venture, partnership, association or any other entity for the conduct of any business. Except as provided in Section 7.1, nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize any Party to act on behalf of any other Party. Non-Interference. Each Party agrees not to interfere with the reasonable and necessary utilization of the Shared Facilities by any other Party as permitted hereunder. Modification and Amendment. The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by all of the Parties. Waiver. The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party’s right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect. Enforceability. Any provision of this Agreement which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of such remaining provisions hereof. Assignment. No Party may assign any of its benefits, rights or obligations hereunder to any third party without the prior written consent of each other Party, provided, however, that any Party may collaterally assign this Agreement to any lender in connection with a financing or a refinancing of its respective Project. Indemnification. Each Party shall indemnify, defend and hold each other Party, its officers, directors, shareholders, members and affiliates, harmless from any and all damages, losses, claims, including claims and actions relating to injury to or death of any person or damage to property, demand, suits, recoveries, costs and expenses, court costs, attorney fees, and all other obligations by or to third parties, arising out of or resulting from the indemnifying Party’s performance or non-performance of its obligations under this Agreement, except in cases of gross negligence or intentional wrongdoing, by the indemnified Party. Choice of Law, Jurisdiction and Waiver of Jury Trial (i) This Agreement and the rights and obligations of the Parties hereunder will be governed pursuant to, and enforced, construed and interpreted in accordance with, the laws of the State of New York without regard to principles of conflicts of laws (other than Section 5-1401 of the General Obligations Law of the State of New York). Venue for resolution of any disputes under this Agreement shall be New York County, New York. (ii) Each of the Parties irrevocably and unconditionally submits to the exclusive jurisdiction of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York for the purposes of any suit, action or other proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement, the transactions contemplated hereby, any provision hereof or the breach, performance, enforcement or validity or invalidity of this Agreement or any provision hereof (and agrees not to commence any suit, action or proceeding relating thereto except in such courts). (iii) THE PARTIES HERETO EACH HEREBY KNOWINGLY, VOLUNTARILY AND INTENTIONALLY WAIVE THE RIGHT EACH MAY HAVE TO A TRIAL BY JURY WITH RESPECT TO ANY PROCEEDINGS BASED HEREON, OR ARISING OUT OF, UNDER OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT, OR ANY COURSE OF CONDUCT, COURSE OF DEALING, STATEMENTS (WHETHER ORAL OR WRITTEN) OR ACTIONS OF EITHER PARTY TO THIS AGREEMENT. THIS PROVISION IS A MATERIAL INDUCEMENT FOR THE PARTIES TO ENTER INTO THIS AGREEMENT. Inspection of Records. Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Shared Facilities held by any other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times. Entire Agreement. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the subject matter hereof. Section Headings. The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof. Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument. Specific Performance. The Parties hereto may demand specific performance of this Agreement. Each Party hereby irrevocably waives any defense based on the adequacy of a remedy at law and any other defense which might be asserted to bar the remedy of specific performance.
